article.headline: Florida Atlantic 93, New Orleans 86
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Carlos Monroe scored 26 points while DeAndre Rice added 18 as Florida Atlantic got a 93-86 Sun Belt Conference win at New Orleans on Thursday. Monroe, the Owls' leading scorer, had missed the last four games due to administrative reasons. James Parlow scored a career-high 29 points, including nine 3-pointers, to lead New Orleans (7-8, 3-1 SBC), while Bo McCalebb had 24. It was the first-ever meeting between the schools. Florida Atlantic (7-7, 3-1) led 47-42 at the half and did not make a turnover until 1:11 left in the frame. Rice scored 12 points, including three 3-pointers in that period. The Owls were 10-of-12 from the field to start the second half and grabbed a 57-43 lead with 16:23 left. New Orleans, which had won five of its last six games, got two 3-pointers from Parlow in the final minute to cut the margin to 89-86 with 26 seconds left. Florida Atlantic, though, got two free throws from Paul Graham III to seal it. Florida Atlantic shot 59 percent overall and was 17-of-22 from the free throw line. New Orleans made a season-high 12 3-pointers.
